  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Plans",
      "body": "Download and familiarize yourself with the plans.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0a9756d17baa645d.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Break down plywood",
      "body": "Using a track saw, break down the plywood. You should have both backs, six shelves, and a board that will be used for both fronts.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/32c53ff9dcde38e8.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Front Template",
      "body": "Using a scrap of 1/4 plywood, layout the front pattern\n\n**Tip:** Using a square to create your radius Hammer a nail into the center then use the square, hooked on the nail.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e652907b2aa4e5a7.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cut Template",
      "body": "Cut 1/4\" Template and sand smooth.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/863f83076f13793c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Layout Fronts",
      "body": "Layout fronts on 3/4\" plywood and cut with bandsaw.\n\n**Tip:** Leave some meat leave between a 1/16\" to an 1/8\" inch of material. we will clean it up with the router in the next step",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d0dbced9b11f2ea6.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Route using the Template",
      "body": "clamp the template to the fronts and route using a pattern bit.\n\n**Tip:** Carpet Tape We used Carpet tape on the narrow part of the template.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/7b8058bc984e3579.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Cap",
      "body": "Cut 1/8\" pine caps using a table saw and glue onto the edge of the plywood fronts.\n\n**Tip:** Use a lot of clamps Bandy Clamps work nice for this.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/4e81177df4f092a5.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Middle Shelves",
      "body": "Cut the radius of the middle shelf and glue the 1/8\" cap the the front edge. Then glue the caps to the remaining shelves.\n\n**Tip:** Use the scrap of wood Use the the scrap remaining from cutting the radius to help when bending the cap around the sharp radius.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/684cc34128b23aaa.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Shelf Pilot Holes",
      "body": "Layout the location for the shelves and drill a 1/8\" pilot hole through both backs.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1af8965dd31f8084.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Drill Pocket Holes",
      "body": "Drill pocket holes on one edge of the Narrow Back.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/de520294d7a12d0c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Glue and Screw the Backs",
      "body": "Screw the Narrow back to the other back.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e58ccb3306f82d3b.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "install the shelves",
      "body": "line up and screw the shelves into position.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d1c8d92f0443cb78.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Glue and clamp the Fronts.",
      "body": "Glue and clamp the fronts into position.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e91466383662fca4.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Visit us for more!",
      "body": "Check out our blog www.RealityDaydream.com for more tutorials and fun project inspiration!"
    }
  ],
